Date: 23/02/26
Name of Interview Panel: Infineon (Chaithra)
Questions:
1. Introduce yourself.
2. When did you start working as an AMS Engineer?
3. Which company did you work for? Was it a service-based company or a product-based company?
4. You recently joined Tessolve. Did they let you know which project or domain you'll be working on?
5. Explain the block diagram of an LDO.
6. If you connect an LDO block to a PLL block, what type of LDO would you choose (high bandwidth or low bandwidth)? Why?
7. Why did you switch from Digital Verification (DV) to AMS?
8. How did you model the LDO?
9. Did you develop the LDO model from scratch, or was it a legacy model? For which client was it developed?
10. Was the LDO used at the SoC level?
11. How confident are you that, if selected at Infineon, you can work at the SoC level?
